====Verb====
{{en-verb2|'''to focus'''|'''[[focuses]] '''or, less commonly,''' [[focusses]]'''|'''[[focused]] '''or, less commonly,''' [[focussed]]'''|'''[[focused]] '''or, less commonly,''' [[focussed]]'''|'''[[focusing]] '''or, less commonly,''' [[focussing]]'''}}

#{{transitive}} To [[adjust]] (a [[lens]]) to position an image with respect to the [[focal plane]].
#:''You'll need to '''focus''' the microscope carefully in order to capture the full detail of this surface.''
#{{transitive}} (''followed by'' '''on''' ''or'' '''upon''') To [[concentrate]] one's [[attention]].
#:''Focus on passing the test.''
#{{transitive}} To make (a liquid) less [[diluted]].
#{{intransitive}} To [[concentrate]] one’s [[attention]].
#:''If you're going to beat your competitors, you need to '''focus'''.''

